The paper discusses the vulnerability of deep neural networks to adversarial attacks in the context of semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the effect of different network architectures and model capacity, which are topics typically studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes defenses against adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of mean-field inference in deep structured models, which is a topic in neural networks (cs.NE).
